Rating: 4
Easy and flavorful vegetarian meal/side that gives you lots of room to play. I pretty much threw in whatever I had on hand and some of the substitutions were because that's just what I had. I used 1 1/3 cup lentils (green - but not French - and yellow), 3 garlic cloves, 1 t salt with the boiling water, about 2 1/3 cups of cut in half cherry tomatoes, 8 green onions thinly sliced, one cucumber sliced and quartered, about 1/2 of an orange bell pepper chopped, 1 can of drained chick peas, 1/2 cup sliced basil, 1/3 cup of chopped cilantro, 4 T of coconut balsamic vinegar, 1/2 cup of olive oil, 2 T of lime, 1 T of dijon, crumbled feta and salt & pepper to taste. I served it with toasted pita with melted havarti cheese. Delicious and flavorful.

