Rating: 3
This is a great vegetarian dish. I cut the oil in half because 1/4 c. seemed excessive. I doubled the garlic and cooked the lentils a bit longer until very tender. I also added the tomatoes to the drained lentils and cooked over low heat approx. 10 minutes (because winter tomatoes in NYC aren't the best). Next time I will only use 2 or 2.5 T red wine vinegar. I served the dish atop toasted whole wheat pita wedges, with a sprinkle of feta and a green salad on the side. Yum!

